          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "EXTB",
                "EDEG",
                "GSPEC",
                "MOSEP",
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " In the deuteron",
                "experiment a stack containing 18 Be foils (thickness",
                "130 um) , Al monitor foils (151 or 102 um) and other",
                "target materials. Irradiated for 1 hour with a 50 nA",
                "deuteron beam of 50 MeV.",
                "For the proton experiments three stacks",
                "were irradiated. In exp1 10 Be (130 um), Al degraders",
                "and monitor (102 um) and other target foils were",
                "irradiated with 25 MeV proton beam (120 nA for 50",
                "min). In exp2 Al monitor (49.6 um) Al degrader (98",
                "um), Ti monitor (10.9 mm), Be ( 285 mm), and other",
                "target foils repeated 25 times were bombarded for 3600",
                "s with a 65 MeV proton beam of 25 nA. In exp3 15 times",
                "repeated sequence of Ti (10.9 um), Be (116.123.135 um),",
                "Ti (10.9 um), Al (98 um), Ti(10.9 um) was irradiated",
                "for 3600 s with 36 MeV proton, beam current of 170 nA.",
                "The beam energy along the stack was preliminary",
                "determined via stopping calculation (Andersen and",
                "Ziegler, 1977) and confirmed by the fitted monitor",
                "reactions."
              ]
            }
          ],
